        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 4 at 1:48PM CDT by NWS Fort Worth TX</headline>
        <description>At 147 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking two strong thunderstorms
near Mexia and near Thornton, moving north at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Mexia around 155 PM CDT.
Wortham around 200 PM CDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Thornton, Ben Hur,
Kosse, Streetman, Tehuacana, Shiloh, Richland, and Kirvin.

This includes Interstate 45 between mile markers 208 and 219.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
